author: COMSOL
description:
A dipolar microwave plasma source sustained by electron cyclotron resonance (ECR) is studied. The power deposition into the plasma from the electromagnetic waves occurs in a very thin resonance zone where the static magnetic flux density is equal to the resonant flux density (0.0875 T).

Requires the Plasma Module, AC/DC Module, and RF Module.
